During the course the students acquire some basic legal terminology, used mainly in the English legal system. Some comparisons of the terms are drawn with other legal systems. The use of legal English is practiced in professional conversations.
Main topics:
What is law? Legal systems.
Sources of law, civil and public law.
Civil and criminal procedure.
Lawyers at work.
Legalese, legal aid in Estonia, separation of powers.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to introduce the basic legal terminology, used mainly in the English legal system, to enable the students to recognize, understand and start using legal terms in order to build up their professional language.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Inglise keeles:
A student who has passed the course is able to
1. recognize and understand basic legal terms in a legal text;
2. use legal terms and collocations in discussions and explain them (important due to difference among legal systems);
3. identify and present relevant information in legal texts.
